cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.MM

This paper deals with the analysis of high-resolution microscopy images of tissue specimens using computer algorithms. The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods for segmentation and classification of tissue images. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of statistical and morphological features for classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep learning methods for segmentation and classification also suggests that it could belong to cs.DL (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of microscopy images, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
